name: Band Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band under your feet, holding the ends with your hands. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and relaxed, and let the band hang in front of your thighs. | Step:3 Engage your traps by shrugging your shoulders upward, lifting the band as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Finger Curls
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your forearm on your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Allow the dumbbell to roll down to your fingertips, then curl it back up by flexing your fingers. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Band Side Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, keeping them parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly bend your elbows and bring your hands towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms still. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly extend your arms back out to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Inner Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on your thighs, allowing the dumbbells to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arm extended over the edge of the bench, holding a dumbbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbell slowly until your arm is fully extended. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbell back up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Hyperextension (On Bench)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the hyperextension bench so that your hips are resting comfortably on the pad and your feet are secured. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. | Step:3 Slowly lower your upper body towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise your upper body back up until it is in line with your legs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline T-Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Lean forward and let your arms hang straight down, perpendicular to the floor. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise them out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a 'T' shape with your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Full Can Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Supinated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, and extend your arm straight up above your shoulder. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Waiter Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms close to your body and your elbows tucked in. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Vertical Leg Raise (On Parallel Bars)
instructions: Step:1 Hang from the parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or slightly higher. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells to your sides with a slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in one hand and your arm extended over the bench, palm facing up. | Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, keeping your wrist in a neutral position. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows bent, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells in front of you, with your palms facing down, until they are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Raise Single Arm Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out to the side, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position, using your chest muscles to lift your body. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm extended.

name: Band Two Legs Calf Raise - (Band Under Both Legs) V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place a resistance band under both feet. | Step:2 Hold the ends of the band with your hands for stability. | Step:3 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, using your calves. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Extension (Across Face)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your chest, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the dumbbell in an arc behind your head until your forearms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then contract your triceps to bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Reverse Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by flexing your elbow. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Band One Arm Overhead Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place one end of the band under your foot. | Step:2 Hold the other end of the band with your arm fully extended overhead, palm facing forward. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl your forearm towards your shoulder, squeezing your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bench Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your head. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Curl (Over Incline Bench)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing forward. | Step:2 Place your other hand on an incline bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on your thigh, allowing your wrist to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Keeping your forearm stationary, curl your wrist upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrist back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Dumbbell Incline Two Arm Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Slowly lie back on the bench, keeping the dumbbells close to your chest. | Step:3 Once you are fully lying down, extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells down towards your forehead, bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Bent Over One Arm Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight back, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your elbows close to your sides, exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Curl Over Incline Bench
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Place your other hand on an incline bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Decline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells slowly behind your head, bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up and elbows resting on the pad. | Step:2 Curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary and your palms facing up. | Step:3 At the top of the curl, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing down. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the starting position as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbells back to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Over Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your head up. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight down towards the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Engaging your shoulder muscles, lift your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Side Lying Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and your head supported by your arm. | Step:2 Hold your upper arm against your side and bend your elbow to curl your forearm towards your shoulder. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Calf Raise (On A Staircase)
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a step or a sturdy platform with your heels hanging off and your toes on the step. | Step:2 Hold onto a railing or wall for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pronate-Grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms facing down, and extend your arms straight up overhead. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head and elbows pointing forward, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Prone Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing your body and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Band Y-Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band in front of your thighs with your palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and lift them up and out to the sides, forming a 'Y' shape with your body. | Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on the edge of a step or platform with your heels hanging off and your toes on the step. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place your other hand on a wall or railing for support. | Step:3 Raise your heel as high as possible, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down below the step. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Hanging Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Palms Up Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Single Leg Reverse Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place the band around the ball of your foot. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the ball of your foot. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Hip Raise (Bent Knee)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides, palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then lift your hips off the ground until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Oblique Knee Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest, twisting your torso to the side as you do so. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side, twisting your torso in the opposite direction. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Prone Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Extend your arm fully, letting it hang straight down towards the floor. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your thighs. | Step:2 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the dumbbells in front of you until they are at shoulder level. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up overhead. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, keeping your arm straight. | Step:3 Bend your elbow and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lateral Raise (Support Head)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Front Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band in front of your thighs with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and lift the band up in front of you until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the band back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Alternate Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Lower one dumbbell down towards your head, bending at the elbow, while keeping the other arm extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and let the dumbbells hang by your sides. | Step:3 Raise your shoulders as high as possible, as if you are trying to touch your ears with your shoulders. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lower Back Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your stomach with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, and slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling your back upwards. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Slowly lift the dumbbells in front of you, with your arms straight, until they are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band in front of your thighs with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and slowly raise them forward until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on the bench with your wrist hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrist upwards, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Incline Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lean back on the bench and raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Keeping your back against the bench, exhale and raise the dumbbells above your head, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing the dumbbells to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your wrists in a neutral position, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying On Floor Rear Delt Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the floor with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Engaging your shoulder muscles, lift your arms up and out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Donkey Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your toes on an elevated surface, such as a step or block. | Step:2 Place your hands on a stable support, such as a wall or railing, for balance. | Step:3 Raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Single Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot off the ground, bending your knee. | Step:3 Slowly curl your right heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstring. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your right foot back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Curl-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl Over Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your elbow on the exercise ball. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Single Leg Calf Raise (On A Dumbbell)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your arm fully extended and close to your body, with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Biceps Leg Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 With your palm facing up, curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Standing Bent Over Two Arm Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Pronated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing down, and extend your arm straight up above your shoulder. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Revers Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on the bench, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the dumbbells towards your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the sides of the bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, slowly raise them up in front of you until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Leg-Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, raising them towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Reverse Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:3 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands, palms facing up, and rest your forearms on your thighs. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells to your sides with a slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your forearm on your thigh. | Step:3 Allow your wrist to extend, letting the dumbbell roll down towards your fingers. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrist back up, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Hyperextension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the hyperextension bench so that your upper thighs are resting on the pad and your feet are secured. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. | Step:3 Lower your upper body towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise your upper body back up until it is in line with your legs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Lying Straight Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your feet together. | Step:2 Place the band around the arches of your feet and hold the ends of the band with your hands. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift both legs off the ground until they are perpendicular to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Lying One Hand Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and your head supported by your arm. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your top hand with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your arm straight, raise the dumbbell up to shoulder height. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Incline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Place your feet flat on the ground and let your arms hang straight down with your palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, shrug your shoulders up towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on the bench, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverse Leg Curl (Bench Support)
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a bench with your hips at the edge and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Hold onto the bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper body still, bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Leg Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying Leg Raise Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a flat bench with your back pressed against it. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Keep your legs straight and together, and lift them up towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Alternating Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your sides and slowly curl one arm up towards your shoulder, squeezing your biceps at the top. | Step:3 Lower the arm back down to the starting position and repeat with the other arm. | Step:4 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bench Hip Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back against the bench and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, then lift your hips off the bench until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Leg Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up by flexing your hips and knees until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Y-Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Lean forward slightly and let your arms hang straight down, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides and up in a Y shape until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place your hands on a wall or stable surface for balance. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, using your calves. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Leg Floor Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place your hands on a wall or sturdy object for balance. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel off the ground, lifting your body up onto the ball of your foot. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Incline Leg Hip Raise (Leg Straight)
instructions: Step:1 Lie on an incline bench with your back flat against the bench and your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the sides of the bench for support. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your legs off the bench, raising them as high as you can while keeping them straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your upper arm against the preacher pad. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Seated Reverse Grip One Arm Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with an underhand grip and extend your arm straight up overhead. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbow, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arm back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Alternating Bicep Curl With Leg Raised On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Place an exercise ball behind you and position one foot on top of it, keeping your balance. | Step:3 With your arms fully extended and elbows close to your sides, curl one dumbbell towards your shoulder while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position and repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your forearms resting on the bench and your palms facing up, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Allow your wrists to hang over the edge of the bench. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Single Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in one hand and your arm fully extended above your chest. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbell in a controlled manner towards your forehead, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:3 Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, then extend your arm back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Standing Front Raise Above Head
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and lift the dumbbells in front of you, raising them above your head. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbells Seated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in both hands with an overhand grip, and raise it above your head. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears. | Step:4 Extend your arms and raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Supine Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Single Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place the band around the ball of your left foot. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly raise your left heel off the ground, lifting your body weight onto the ball of your foot. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your left heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the right leg.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on the bench with your wrist hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrist upwards, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a mat or bench with your legs extended. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides or under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lift your feet off the ground, bringing your thighs towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell High Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms stationary and curl the dumbbells as high as possible while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, hanging towards the floor. | Step:2 Keep your arm straight and lift the dumbbell out to the side, away from your body. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Rotated Dumbbell Pronate-Grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands, palms facing down, and extend your arms straight up overhead. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms close to your head and elbows pointing forward, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on rotated movement.

name: Dynamic Style Band Side Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with both hands, palms facing down. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, keeping them parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly bend your elbows and bring your hands towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms still. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly extend your arms back out to the starting position. | Step:5 (dynamic variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intermediate Style Dumbbell Preacher Curl Over Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your elbow on the exercise ball. | Step:3 (intermediate variation) Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Prone Hammer Curl - Macro Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing your body and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keep your upper arm stationary and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms. Focus on macro movement.

name: Dumbbell Over Bench One Arm Wrist Curl - Strength Variation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing down. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on the bench with your wrist hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Slowly curl your wrist upwards, bringing the dumbbell towards your forearm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. Maintain strength form throughout. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Lying Leg-Hip Raise - Contracted Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, raising them towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. Emphasize contracted control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hanging Straight Leg Raise With Elevated
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or as high as you can comfortably go. Maintain elevated form throughout. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Targeted Style Single Leg Calf Raise (On A Dumbbell)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. Emphasize targeted control. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Firm Style Hanging Oblique Knee Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest, twisting your torso to the side as you do so. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side, twisting your torso in the opposite direction. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions. Emphasize firm control.

name: Push-Up Inside Leg Kick
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 As you push back up, lift one leg off the ground and kick it out to the side, keeping it straight. | Step:4 Lower your leg back down and repeat the push-up, then switch to the other leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating leg kicks with each push-up repetition.

name: Kettlebell Goblet Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, lower your body down into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward, and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Arm Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out in front of you and place your palm against the wall. | Step:3 Engage your core and lean your body forward, keeping your arm straight and your back flat. | Step:4 Slowly push against the wall with your palm, activating your lat muscles. | Step:5 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and repeat with the other arm.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands placed close together, directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, letting it hang down by your side. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, slowly bend sideways at the waist towards the opposite side of the dumbbell, lowering the weight as far as you comfortably can. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Chest Dip On Straight Bar
instructions: Step:1 Grab the parallel bars with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Bend your knees and cross your ankles. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your arms until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Biceps Curl To Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows close to your sides, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Once your forearms are vertical, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:5 Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position by reversing the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Arms Apart Circular Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Keeping your legs straight, bend forward at the waist and reach down towards your toes with your right hand. | Step:3 As you reach down, simultaneously lift your left leg straight up behind you, maintaining balance. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left hand reaching towards your toes and your right leg lifting up behind you. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Palm Up
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place it on top of your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Lift one leg off the ground and extend it in front of you, keeping your knee slightly bent. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Lying External Shoulder Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side on a flat bench with your upper arm against your side and your elbow bent 90 degrees. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your hand with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm against your side, slowly rotate your forearm upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing your torso to lean forward. | Step:3 Continue lowering the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one kettlebell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back to shoulder height. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bottoms-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring them towards your chest, keeping your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your hips off the ground, bringing your knees towards your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Decline Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting on your chest. | Step:2 Place your feet flat on the ground and keep your back pressed against the bench. | Step:3 Extend your arm and push the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, fully extending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Seated Revers Grip Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Sphinx
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the ground with your forearms flat on the floor, elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest off the ground, keeping your forearms and toes on the floor. | Step:3 Hold this position for a few seconds, making sure to keep your neck in a neutral position. | Step:4 Slowly lower your chest back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Kneeling Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Kneel down on the ground with your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you, shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Extend your legs straight behind you, balancing on your toes and hands, forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your upper body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Upright Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Rotate your arms externally, bringing the dumbbells up towards your head while keeping your elbows in the same position. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the band with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and wrap it around your fingers. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, with your wrists hanging off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Tuck Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your shoulder blades off the ground and bring your knees towards your chest, simultaneously curling your upper body towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your shoulder blades and extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Incline Side Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:5 Lower your hips back down to the ground and repeat on the other side.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Carry
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you walk forward, maintaining the dumbbell overhead. | Step:4 Continue walking for the desired distance or time. | Step:5 Switch hands and repeat the exercise.

name: Elevator
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or cross them in front of your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly bend forward at the waist, lowering your upper body towards the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise your upper body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickbacks On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate your palms to face forward. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbells up to your shoulders while keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing away from your body. | Step:5 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your palms back to facing your body. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended along your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your feet off the ground, bringing your thighs perpendicular to the floor. | Step:3 Contract your abs and curl your hips off the floor, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body, arms extended downwards. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and knees, lowering the dumbbells towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Push through your heels and extend your hips and knees, lifting the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kneeling Bicep Curl Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor with an exercise ball in front of you. | Step:2 Place your elbows on top of the exercise ball, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl With Stork Stance
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Extend one leg behind you, balancing on the toes of that foot. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Full Maltese
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides. | Step:2 Slowly lean forward, keeping your arms straight, until your upper body is parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engage your core and hold this position for a few seconds. | Step:4 Return to the starting position by pushing through your feet and standing back up. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). | Step:3 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Triceps Dip (Between Benches)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge of the bench, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide-Grip Chest Dip On High Parallel Bars
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body suspended in the air. | Step:2 Lean forward slightly and lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest is just above the bars. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your hips forward off the bench and straighten your legs, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a suspension trainer with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and place the top of your foot in the foot cradle of the suspension trainer. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your chest up and your knee in line with your toes. | Step:4 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Single Leg Bridge With Outstretched Leg
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Hold for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Seated Calf Stretch (Male)
