instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair or bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your calf muscle. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Side-To-Side Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Bend at the waist to the right, reaching your right hand towards your right foot while keeping your left hand extended to the side. | Step:3 Return to the starting position and then bend at the waist to the left, reaching your left hand towards your left foot while keeping your right hand extended to the side. | Step:4 Repeat the side-to-side bending motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lateral To Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Next, raise your arms in front of you until they are parallel to the ground, again keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:2 Lean forward and position your upper arm against the inside of your thigh. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm slightly bent and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Concentration Curl (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm extended down towards the floor. | Step:3 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Alternating Seated Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell while rotating your forearm until your palm is facing your shoulder. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the curl with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating curls for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbows and bringing your chest towards the bar. | Step:4 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Lower Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on your thighs or on the sides of the chair for support. | Step:3 Slowly lean forward from your hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your lower back and hold for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Slowly return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling Push-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your hands shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, so that your body forms a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your chest is just above the ground, then push back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Pelvic Tilt
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or let them hang by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and tilt your pelvis forward, pushing your lower back towards the wall behind you. | Step:4 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying (Side) Quads Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight. | Step:2 Bend your top leg and grab your ankle or foot with your hand. | Step:3 Gently pull your ankle or foot towards your glutes until you feel a stretch in your quads. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release the stretch and repeat on the other side.

name: Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit upright with your back straight. | Step:2 Extend one arm overhead, bending it at the elbow. | Step:3 Place your opposite hand on the bent elbow and gently pull it towards your head. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling a gentle stretch in your triceps. | Step:5 Release the stretch and repeat on the other arm.

name: Squat To Overhead Reach With Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you come up from the squat, raise your arms overhead and twist your torso to one side. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the squat, this time twisting your torso to the opposite side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides with each squat repetition.

name: Kettlebell Plyo Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands on the kettlebells, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Push through your hands explosively, lifting your hands off the kettlebells and extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Land softly back on the kettlebells and immediately lower your chest back down for the next repetition. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapula Dips
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows and retracting your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to squeeze a pencil between them. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to extend your elbows and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Inner Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the bench, allowing your elbows to hang down and your palms to face forward. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair Leg Extended Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your quadriceps. | Step:4 Hold this position for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Single Arm Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and one hand placed slightly wider than the other. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, shift your weight to one side and lift the opposite arm off the ground, extending it straight out to the side. | Step:4 Push through your chest and triceps to raise your body back up to the starting position, while simultaneously lowering your extended arm back to the ground. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, alternating the arm you extend with each repetition.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Deltoid Rear
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing inwards. | Step:2 Extend your arm straight down towards the floor, keeping it close to your body. | Step:3 Raise your arm up and back, squeezing your shoulder blade towards your spine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Kettlebell Seesaw Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one kettlebell overhead while keeping the other kettlebell at shoulder height. | Step:3 Lower the pressed kettlebell back to shoulder height while simultaneously pressing the other kettlebell overhead. | Step:4 Continue alternating the pressing motion, creating a seesaw-like movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Standing Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing forward and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight upward while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Jackknife Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms overhead. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs and upper body simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your palms facing forward and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells slowly to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, with your body forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the elevated surface by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Set up a decline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended towards the floor. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, raise your shoulders towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Supported Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, slowly lower your body down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plyo Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:3 Push explosively off the ground, using your chest muscles to propel your upper body off the ground. | Step:4 Land softly with your hands back in the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Bicycle Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your hands behind your head and your knees bent. | Step:2 Lift your feet off the ground and bring your right knee towards your chest while simultaneously twisting your torso to bring your left elbow towards your right knee. | Step:3 Straighten your right leg while bringing your left knee towards your chest and twisting your torso to bring your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:4 Continue alternating the twisting motion, as if you are pedaling a bicycle, while keeping your core engaged throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with the band placed just above your knees. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, push your hips back and bend your knees to lower into a squat position. | Step:3 Make sure your knees are tracking over your toes and your weight is in your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:3 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Press one dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder level. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Overhead Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm overhead, bending at the elbow so that your hand reaches towards the opposite shoulder blade. | Step:3 With your other hand, gently pull the elbow of the extended arm towards the opposite side of your head, feeling a stretch in your triceps. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up (On Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Start by getting on your hands and knees, with your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your upper body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Pause for a moment when your chest is just above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lean Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly shift your weight forward, bringing your shoulders past your hands. | Step:3 Keep your elbows slightly bent and your body straight as you lean forward. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Iron Cross
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, forming a T shape with your body. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up On Lower Arms
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your forearms on the ground and elbows directly below your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Straddle Maltese
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pair of rings with your arms fully extended and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Spread your legs wide apart, forming a straddle position. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lower your body until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl Reverse
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, then squeeze your glutes and push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting on your thigh. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and position the dumbbell at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbell upward and slightly inward, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Korean Dips
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your arms extended and supporting your body weight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl V Sit On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bosu ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head until you feel a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cocoons
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Hip (On Parallel Bars)
instructions: Step:1 Stand between two parallel bars with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bars and lift your body off the ground, supporting your weight on your arms. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly lift your legs to the side, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supine Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternate Heel Touchers
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your shoulders off the ground and reach your right hand towards your right heel. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat on the left side, reaching your left hand towards your left heel. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supination On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your legs extended and your arms by your sides, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Rotate your palms to face up, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, squeezing your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Bend your left knee and lower your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, stepping back with your left foot.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Hammer Grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place one foot on a raised surface, such as a step or block, with your heel hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with a hammer grip, meaning your palms are facing each other and your fingers are wrapped around the handle. | Step:4 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Band Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your legs spread apart and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold one end of the band in your hand and step on the other end with your foot on the same side. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly and rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 With your palm facing up, slowly curl your hand towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hand back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating arms.

name: Spider Crawl Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Bring your right knee towards your right elbow, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 As you bring your right knee back, simultaneously lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position and repeat with your left knee towards your left elbow. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Swing 360
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engage your core and swing your arms in a circular motion, rotating your torso as you do so. | Step:4 Continue the circular motion, swinging your arms and rotating your torso for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:5 Remember to breathe throughout the exercise.

name: Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise one dumbbell in front of you until it is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:6 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand, with your palms facing towards your feet and your arms extended straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Lower one kettlebell down towards your shoulder while keeping the other kettlebell extended straight up. | Step:4 Press the lowered kettlebell back up to the starting position while simultaneously lowering the other kettlebell down towards your shoulder. | Step:5 Continue alternating the press motion with each kettlebell for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twisted Leg Raise (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your legs off the ground, bringing them towards your chest. | Step:3 As you lift your legs, twist your hips to one side, bringing your knees towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your hips to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm straight and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Cuban Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keeping your core engaged and your elbows slightly bent, press the dumbbells up and overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the starting position as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the incline bench and let your elbows hang down, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Extended Range One Arm Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in one hand, with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow locked and your wrist straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Military Press To The Side
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Glute Bridge Two Legs On Bench (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your back against it and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, then lift your hips off the bench until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push-Up (On Box)
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the edge of a box or elevated surface, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the box by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Elbow Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other and arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then press the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your elbows. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and position the dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells up and away from your body until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Shoulder Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest the dumbbells on your thighs and lean back onto the bench. | Step:3 Use your thighs to help raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, then rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Exhale and slowly raise the dumbbells above your head, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Place your free hand on your thigh for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Crunch (Hands Overhead)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight above your head. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot and a smaller step back with your left foot. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your left knee slightly above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Exercise Ball On The Wall Calf Raise (Tennis Ball Between Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and place an exercise ball between your lower back and the wall. | Step:2 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly in front of you. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms extended by your sides. | Step:4 Place a tennis ball between your knees. | Step:5 Raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Neutral Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and your arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your chest against the backrest and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down with your palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Arm Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your torso forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight back, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Frog Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 As you lower your body, lift your feet off the ground and bring your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then extend your legs back out and push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place a band around your upper arms, just above the elbows. | Step:2 Assume a push-up position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Seated Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Lower the kettlebells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Femoral
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and a dumbbell resting on your lower abdomen. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring the dumbbell towards your glutes, keeping your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and position your feet so that your front foot is flat on the ground and your back foot is elevated on a bench or step. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, keeping your back knee slightly bent and your back heel off the ground. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Quick Feet V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Begin by rapidly moving your feet up and down, as if you were running in place. | Step:3 Keep your movements quick and light, focusing on staying on the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lunge With Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. Your right knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle and your left knee should be hovering just above the ground. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, simultaneously curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the lunge, then push through your right heel to return to the starting position, lowering the dumbbells back down to your sides. | Step:5 Repeat the lunge and bicep curl on the opposite side, stepping forward with your left foot. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cross Body Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the dumbbells across your body towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart and a dumbbell in one hand, resting your elbow on the inside of your thigh. | Step:2 Fully extend your arm and hold the dumbbell with an underhand grip. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Suspended Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees up towards your chest, curling your pelvis towards your ribcage. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your knees back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flutter Kicks
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your hands by your sides. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground about 6 inches. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, alternate lifting one leg slightly higher than the other. | Step:4 Continue this fluttering motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the ground slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with your feet elevated on a stable surface. | Step:2 Keep your body in a straight line from head to toe, engaging your core muscles. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
